GOVERNOR Bala Mohammed of Bauchi State took a new wife in Lagos on Friday. She is Natasha Mariana, a Lebanese-Nigerian. The modest ceremony took place at the Syrian mosque in Ikoyi, Lagos followed by a dinner attended by relations and close friends of the family. The 60-year-old PDP chieftain was the Federal Capital Territory Minister in the Jonathan Administration. He defeated Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the March governorship election. 